"The bottom line is that as costs rise, people from the middle to the low [income scale] will try to supplement their income wherever they can," said Song Seng Wun, an economist at Malaysian bank CIMB.
Historically high gold prices over the past two years have contributed to people hastily pawning their personal belongings and taking the opportunity to exchange their family jewelry for cash.
About 70 percent of the items pledged at the city's 200 pawnshops are gold.
People say, "The price of gold looks good, we'll pawn Grandma's gold necklace and get it back next month."
Thailand's largest pawnshop operator, EasyMoney, has seen a 20 percent increase in the number of customers using its pawnshops in recent months.
Growth in the pawn industry is so great that ValueMax, operator of a branch in the Bendemeer centre and 15 similar ones in Singapore, plans to expand not only into neighbouring Malaysia – where it has four branches – but also outside Asia, says ValueMax CEO yes Lee Ching.
The company will fund this by using 60 percent of the SGD 66 million it raised on the Singapore Stock Exchange this week.
While some discount lenders have come under fire for high interest rates, Ms. yes says the pledge not only offers lower rates than other lenders, but it also doesn't directly increase debt.
"Customers are pawning items they already own, and monetizing personal assets doesn't increase household debt," he says.
In society, pledge of assets is increasingly accepted as a means of securing short-term, secure financing.
Moreover, it is not only people in financial distress who use pawnshops.
Wealthy people in Singapore also use ValueMax branches to pawn gold bars or Rolex watches, and can get up to 60 percent of the purchase price in cash.
Our customers come from all possible backgrounds.
"These include wealthy individuals who need to borrow for the short term because of their bold deals or investments, or small businesses that need help resolving their cash flow issues," says Ms. yes.
Sometimes they just need money as quickly as possible.
