Fire brigades arrived to rescue a lost puppy that was stuck 15 meters above the ground on a dangerous protrusion in a quarry
Cocker Spaniel Ruby escaped after a small car accident.
Three days later, he was spotted trapped in a quarry by a man walking his dog.
Firefighters rappelled down the rock face to save the dog from certain death.
The puppy was rescued by fire brigades who came to rescue him after he somehow trapped himself on a dangerous protrusion in a quarry 15 meters above the ground.
Nine-month-old Cocker Spaniel Ruby escaped after a small car accident on Sunday afternoon, and survived alone for three days until he was rescued from the quarry on Wednesday.
